 grind <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides and base of mixing bowl with spatula then grind again <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Add 300 g reserved filling and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place chocolate in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then melt <b>1 min 30 sec\/50°C\/speed 3<b>. Scrape down with spatula then melt again <b>1 min\/50°C\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Add remaining 300 g filling and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>. Pour into tin over biscuit layer."},{"content":"Gently pour reserved peanut butter mixture over chocolate layer."},{"content":"Bake for 50 minutes (150°C) until almost set. Allow to cool in tin for 1 hour before carefully running a knife around edge of tin and removing. Place on a serving plate or cake stand. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make topping."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Topping"},{"content":"Place milk chocolate and cream in mixing bowl then melt <b>3 min\/60°C\/speed 1<b>. Set aside to thicken for 30 minutes then pour over top of cheesecake, allowing it to drizzle down sides. Refrigerate for at least 3 hours (or overnight) to set. Meanwhile, prepare peanut brittle."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Peanut Brittle Decoration"},{"content":"Line a baking tray with baking paper. Heat sugar in a dry frying pan over a medium heat, without stirring, until sugar begins to clump together. Swirl and tilt pan until sugar is completely molten and turns caramel in colour - do not be tempted to stir as this will cause the caramel to crystalise."},{"content":"Stir in peanuts then immediately pour peanut mixture onto prepared baking tray. Quickly spread mixture to 5 mm thick using the back of a metal spoon. Set aside to cool completely (approx. 15 minutes)."},{"content":"When ready to serve, break up peanut brittle and arrange over top of cheesecake before slicing."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Shop bought peanut butter 